### Element Operators

#!markdown

**Single**

Exact one item exist othewise throw exception

**SingleOrDefault**

Exact one or returns default (i.e. null or 0 etc depending on datatype) if no item exist

#!csharp

var singleCustomerInLambdaSyntax = customers.Single(c => c.CustomerId == 8);
singleCustomerInLambdaSyntax.Display();

var singleCustomerInQuerySyntax = (from c in customers
                                    where c.CustomerId == 8
                                    select c).Single();
singleCustomerInQuerySyntax.Display();

var singleOrDefaultCustomerInLambdaSyntax = customers.SingleOrDefault(c => c.CustomerId == 88);
singleOrDefaultCustomerInLambdaSyntax.Display();

#!markdown

**First** first item if eixist, thorws exception if not exist

**FirstOrDefault** first item if exist, or return default value

**Last** last item if eixist, thorws exception if not exist

**LastOrDefault** last item if exist, or return default value

**ElementAt** item at index if eixist, thorws exception if not exist

**ElementAtOrDefault** item at index if exist, or return default value

#!csharp

customers.First().Display();
customers.Where(c => c.CustomerId == 100).FirstOrDefault()().Display();
